31/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- In its session on Wednesday (30 August), the government appointed Ljupcho Todorovski as new director of the Bureau for Public Security and Alexander Miyalkov as head of the Security and Counter-Intelligence Service.
Todorovski was the head of the anti-drug department and tasked with fighting organised crime under the interior ministry.
Four years ago, Miyalkov headed military counter-intelligence but later moved to the private sector.
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, Focus - 30/08/06)
